{"name":"Sleet","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Essentially frozen rain, sleet has the same effect as light snow, but any accumulation typically doesn&rsquo;t last longer than 1&ndash;2 hours after the storm.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Snow, Light</strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">: Light snow reduces visibility to three-quarters of the normal range, resulting in a &ndash;2 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. Light snow has a 75% chance each hour of extinguishing unprotected flames and imposes a &ndash;2 penalty on ranged attacks. Light snow does not impede movement unless it continues for 2 or more hours, at which point moving into a square of such snow requires 1 extra 5-foot square of movement (this stacks with difficult terrain). Every 2 hours of light snow leaves 1 inch of snow on the ground. As long as at least 2 inches of snow remain on the ground, the requirement of an extra square of movement to enter a square of snow persists. If at least 1 foot of snow remains on the ground, entering a snow-filled square instead requires 2 extra squares of movement.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Sleet"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.qlOnfxRNzNpn75pu"}},"_id":"EDjkISvKG8g9UZsK"}
{"name":"Snow, Light","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Light snow reduces visibility to three-quarters of the normal range, resulting in a &ndash;2 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. Light snow has a 75% chance each hour of extinguishing unprotected flames and imposes a &ndash;2 penalty on ranged attacks. Light snow does not impede movement unless it continues for 2 or more hours, at which point moving into a square of such snow requires 1 extra 5-foot square of movement (this stacks with difficult terrain). Every 2 hours of light snow leaves 1 inch of snow on the ground. As long as at least 2 inches of snow remain on the ground, the requirement of an extra square of movement to enter a square of snow persists. If at least 1 foot of snow remains on the ground, entering a snow-filled square instead requires 2 extra squares of movement.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Snow, Light"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.J0mLe24nyimqwbzT"}},"_id":"FgU0iYmNC2Qzg3TV"}
{"_id":"LFVpNkGHMMzngeaT","name":"Haboob","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">A haboob is a sandstorm created by a thunderstorm. See Sandstorm below for its effects.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Sandstorm</strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">: Sandstorms occur when severe or greater winds kick up sand and debris in a desert or similarly arid environment. Sandstorms reduce visibility to 1d10&times;10 feet, and those within them take a &ndash;6 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;checks. Sandstorms deal 1d3 points of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> per hour to creatures caught in the open.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"yjm4iwz8","formula":"-6","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Haboob"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}}}
{"name":"Drizzle","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Drizzle reduces visibility to three-quarters of the normal range, imposing a &ndash;2 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. It automatically extinguishes tiny unprotected flames (candles and the like, but not torches).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"yjm4iwz8","formula":"-2","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Drizzle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}},"_id":"MWutlj6oo6R0CL8K"}
{"name":"Rain","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Rain reduces visibility ranges by half, resulting in a &ndash;4 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. Rain automatically extinguishes unprotected flames (candles, torches, and the like) and imposes a &ndash;4 penalty on ranged attacks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Rain"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.G2NoJNEbNTc2c2vS"}},"_id":"N4hJCfLWVR6fMiRv"}
{"name":"Fog, Medium","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Medium fog reduces visibility ranges by half, resulting in a &ndash;4 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks and a &ndash;4 penalty on ranged attacks. Medium fog typically occurs early in the day, late in the day, or sometimes at night, but the heat of the midday usually burns it away. Medium fog occurs only when there is no or light wind.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Fog, Medium"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.BlM0z806Pgp5UGvg"}},"_id":"RJbtH2eCzm220Urm"}
{"name":"Windstorm","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wind Strength</strong>: This is the category of the wind strength.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wind Speed</strong>: This is the range of wind speeds that occur. Wind speed typically fluctuates between these values through the period of the day, and for moderate or higher wind strength, there are periods in the day when the wind speed dips below the listed range.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ranged Weapon Penalty/Siege Weapon Penalty</strong>: These are the penalties that characters take when firing ranged weapons and siege weapons in wind of the listed strength. In windstorm-strength wind, normal ranged weapon attacks (either projectile or thrown) are impossible. This includes ranged attacks made via spells of the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Conjuration\">conjuration</a>&nbsp;school, but it does not include&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Evocation\">evocation</a>&nbsp;ranged attacks. Siege weapons include all weapons of that type and boulders thrown by&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/humanoids/giants\">giants</a>&nbsp;and other creatures with the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Rock-Throwing-Ex-\">rock throwing</a>&nbsp;special attack.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Check Size</strong>: Creatures of the listed size or smaller are unable to move forward against the force of the wind unless they succeed at a DC 10&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;check (on the ground) or a DC 20&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly\">Fly</a>&nbsp;check if airborne.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Blown Away Size</strong>: Creatures of the listed size on the ground are knocked&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Prone\">prone</a>, roll 1d4&times;10 feet, and take 2d6 points of&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a>, unless they succeed on a DC 15&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;check. Flying creatures of the listed size are blown back 2d6&times;10 feet and take 2d6 points of&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a>&nbsp;due to battering and buffeting, unless they succeed at a DC 25&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly\">Fly</a>&nbsp;check.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Skill Penalty</strong>: This is the penalty for skill checks that can be affected by the wind. These penalties always apply on&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly\">Fly</a>&nbsp;checks and sound-based&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a>&nbsp;checks, but GMs may also wish to apply them on&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics\">Acrobatics</a>&nbsp;checks,&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\">Climb</a> checks, and any other ability or skill checks that could be adversely affected by winds.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[{"text":"Ranged Attacks Not  Possible / [[-4]] Siege Weapon Penalty\nThese are the penalties that characters take when firing ranged weapons and siege weapons in wind of the listed strength. In windstorm-strength wind, normal ranged weapon attacks (either projectile or thrown) are impossible. This includes ranged attacks made via spells of the conjuration school, but it does not include evocation ranged attacks. Siege weapons include all weapons of that type and boulders thrown by giants and other creatures with the rock throwing special attack.","subTarget":"ranged"},{"text":"[[-8]]\nThis is the penalty for skill checks that can be affected by the wind. These penalties always apply on Fly checks and sound-based Perception checks, but GMs may also wish to apply them on Acrobatics checks, Climb checks, and any other ability or skill checks that could be adversely affected by winds.","subTarget":"skills"}],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Windstorm"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}},"_id":"aMcZxcigUnSMMGYz"}
{"_id":"b6ogG0XE8y076bRC","name":"Blizzard","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">A combination of severe or stronger winds with heavy snow can create blizzard conditions. Blizzards reduce range of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/v/vision\">vision</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;to no more than 20 feet, and even then, creatures takes a &ndash;8 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;checks within that range. In a blizzard, the snowfall increases to 4 inches of snow each hour, and travel in more than 3 feet of snow is usually impossible without&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/goods-and-services/containers-bags-boxes-more#TOC-Snowshoes\">snowshoes</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> or an ability such as waterwalk. Furthermore, the high winds make it feel (and affect living creatures) as if the temperature were 20&deg; F colder. There is a 20% chance that a blizzard lasts for 2d12 hours instead of the normal duration for heavy snow.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"yjm4iwz8","formula":"-8","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Blizzard"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}}}
{"name":"Fog, Heavy","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Heavy fog obscures all vision beyond 5 feet, including&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Darkvision\">darkvision</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">. Creatures 5 feet away have&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Concealment\">concealment</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">. Heavy fog typically occurs early in the day, late in the day, or sometimes at night, but the heat of the midday usually burns it away. Heavy fog occurs only when there is no or light wind.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[{"text":"Heavy fog obscures all vision beyond 5 feet, including darkvision. Creatures 5 feet away have concealment. Heavy fog typically occurs early in the day, late in the day, or sometimes at night, but the heat of the midday usually burns it away. Heavy fog occurs only when there is no or light wind.","subTarget":"skill.per"}],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Fog, Heavy"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.Evy5UQSU8FjmUuVo"}},"_id":"eFUaL2dkqbDGN1z6"}
{"_id":"hYPYhg6UNsYVFkEQ","name":"Sandstorm","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Sandstorms occur when severe or greater winds kick up sand and debris in a desert or similarly arid environment. Sandstorms reduce visibility to 1d10&times;10 feet, and those within them take a &ndash;6 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;checks. Sandstorms deal 1d3 points of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> per hour to creatures caught in the open.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"wm3ntywb","formula":"-6","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Sandstorm"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}}}
{"name":"Snow, Medium","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Medium snow reduces visibility ranges by half, resulting in a &ndash;4 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. Medium snow extinguishes unprotected flames and imposes a &ndash;4 penalty on ranged attacks. Medium snow does not impede movement unless it continues for 1 hour, at which point moving into a square of such snow requires 1 extra 5-foot square of movement (this stacks with difficult terrain). Every hour of medium snow leaves 1 inch of snow on the ground. As long as at least 2 inches of snow remain on the ground, the requirement of an extra square of movement to enter a square of snow persists. If at least 1 foot of snow remains on the ground, entering a snow-filled square instead requires 2 extra squares of movement.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-4","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Snow, Medium"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.9esxelCiJVffbONb"}},"_id":"j9HIyM0isKCGhQHz"}
{"_id":"ldtZ7CtL2s1Ot6Y1","name":"Tornado","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">With winds with speeds of 174&ndash;300 miles per hour, tornados are deadly terrors. The smallest tornados occupy a 20-foot-radius burst, with winds of windstorm strength swirling up to 100 feet beyond that burst. The largest tornados can be 100-foot-radius bursts, with a windstorm whose radius extends 500 feet beyond that burst. Ranged attacks, including normal, siege, and even those produced by&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Evocation\">evocation</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;spells, are impossible in the core burst of a tornado. Huge or smaller creatures must succeed a DC 20&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;check or be sucked up by the funnel of the tornado; this deals 8d8 points of bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing lethal damage to the creatures. This damage ignores all but&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Damage-Reduction-Ex-or-Su-\">DR</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">/epic,&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Damage-Reduction-Ex-or-Su-\">DR</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">/&mdash;, and&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/damaging-objects#TOC-Hardness\">hardness</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">. Once it deals this damage, the tornado flings the creature it has sucked up 1d20&times;10 feet up and away from the tornado, dealing 1d6 points of falling damage per 10 feet that the creature is flung. Gargantuan and larger creatures take the 8d8 points of damage but are not moved by the tornado. A tornado moves at a speed of 40 feet, though the direction it moves is entirely unpredictable&mdash;you can determine the direction randomly each round. Tornados typically last for 3d6 minutes, but some can swirl for up to an hour. While most tornados are created by thunderstorms, some smaller tornados (typically with a 5- to 10-foot-burst radius, with no outer radius) can be created in areas of wildfire (firenados), snow (snownados), or sand (dust&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Devil\">devils</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">). They deal a similar amount of damage, but firenados deal fire damage, snownados deal cold damage, and dust&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Devil\">devils</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> deal bludgeoning damage only, and these types of tornados do not fling their targets.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[{"text":"Ranged attacks, including normal, siege, and even those produced by evocation spells, are impossible in the core burst of a tornado.","subTarget":"ranged"}],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Tornado"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}}}
