{"_id":"sYmTMPQ80593LqKt","name":"Hurricane","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Hurricanes are incredibly massive storms featuring heavy rain and a wind strength greater than that of the most powerful windstorm. With winds of 75&ndash;174 miles per hour, a hurricane renders ranged attacks impossible, and siege weapons take a &ndash;8 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">. Large or smaller creatures must succeed at a DC 15&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;check or they are unable to move forward against the strength of the wind. Medium or smaller creatures on the ground must succeed at a DC 15&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;check or they are knocked&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Prone\">prone</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;and roll 1d6x10 feet, taking 1d6 points of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;per 10 feet. Flying creatures must succeed at a DC 25&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly\">Fly</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;check or they are blown back 2d8&times;10 feet and take 4d6 points of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> due to battering and buffeting. Hurricanes also usually cause flooding. It&rsquo;s nearly impossible to journey out into a hurricane unscathed.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[{"text":"A hurricane renders ranged attacks impossible, and siege weapons take a [[–8]] penalty on attack rolls","subTarget":"ranged"}],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Hurricane"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.precipitation-weather-buffs.N2k02h1svfKyyOu4"}}}
{"name":"Snow, Heavy","type":"buff","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/island.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Heavy snow reduces visibility ranges to one-quarter of the normal range, resulting in a &ndash;6 penalty on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\"> checks. It extinguishes unprotected flames and imposes a &ndash;6 penalty on ranged attacks. Heavy snow impedes movement even before it begins to stick. Moving into a square during a heavy snowstorm requires 1 extra 5-foot square of movement (this stacks with difficult terrain). Every hour of heavy snow leaves 1d4 inches of snow on the ground. As long as at least 2 inches of snow remain on the ground, the requirement of an extra square of movement to enter a square of snow persists. If at least 1 foot of snow remains on the ground, 2 extra squares of movement are required to enter a snow-filled square instead. A heavy snowstorm has a 10% chance of generating thundersnow and has a 40% chance of becoming a blizzard if the wind speed is severe or stronger.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"npo56f8a","formula":"-6","operator":"add","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"o4p4avy4","formula":"-6","operator":"add","subTarget":"rattack","modifier":"penalty","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"buffType":"temp","active":true,"level":null,"duration":{"value":"","units":"","start":0},"hideFromToken":false,"identifiedName":"Snow, Heavy"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"BtAhBRW9P5xaS8hf":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium